      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IM BIG BUSINESS (6) settled close to the pace from the ace starting position then took over in front and maintained the advantage to take out a 1800m race at this track last start, a deserved win on the back of some solid recent performances. It doesn't get any easier but he is capable of another big performance. DELIGHTFUL DREAM (5) worked to find the lead and kept kicking to make it two consecutive wins since resuming last time out over 1800m here, getting home 11 metres ahead of his rivals. Taking on a better line-up this time but he good enough to play a major role. CENTREFOLD STAR (3) returns from a spell of four months. Honest type who has won first-up in the past. Best form reads well so a winning return is on the cards. HAWKESDALE DEED (2) is tough to leave out on the back of two successive wins, most recently at Mt Gambier three-and-a-half weeks ago. Include from the favourable draw.",
